               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Khulasat al-tawarikh by Sūjan Rāʾi, fl. 1690-1698
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="CODRINGTON.READE_NO_66_BOX_33-item1">
                     <author key="person_28973620" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/28973620/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Sūjan Rāʾi, fl. 1690-1698</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">منشی سجان رای <addName xml:lang="fa" type="nisbah">استرابادي</addName>
                        </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">منشی سنجان رای</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="alt">منشی سوجن رای</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9453">Khulasat al-tawarikh.</title>
                     <note>Bound in at front. One folio with partial index in English, on watermarked paper. Six folios with index in Persian; the first is misplaced and should be last. Folio one, verso: Presented by Lieutenant Colonel James Tod January 5, 1828. Inside front cover, after title in Roman script: J. Tod Captn. Pol. Agent Western Rajpoot States Oodipoor 1818. Copied by Moonshee Bindraban from an old MSS. A general history of India, from the earliest times to the death of Aurangzib. Copied from a MS written by Muhammad Fadil b. Karamallah Khaksar, whose lengthy colophon is preserved. Some rubrication.</note>
                     <incipit>Incipit:</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp 453-8.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, 229-31.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 362.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Donations register for November 15 1851 mentions 3 Persian MSS as included in Tod's bequest, without any details.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
